## Ejecucion Local

### Backend

```bash
cd Backend
npm install
cp .env.example .env
npm run start:dev
```

Variables clave (`Backend/.env`):

```env
PORT=3000
DATABASE_URL=
DB_SSL=false
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:5173

JWT_SECRET=replace_with_a_long_random_secret
APP_URL=http://localhost:5173

GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

GEMINI_API_KEY=

SMTP_HOST=smtp-relay.brevo.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=
SMTP_PASS=
MAIL_FROM=no-reply@klarity.local

SEED_DEFAULT_PASSWORD=
SEED_ADVISOR_PASSWORD=
SEED_ADMIN_PASSWORD=
SEED_DEMO_PASSWORD=
```

### Frontend

```bash
cd Frontend
npm install
node server.js
# o bien: servir Frontend/public con cualquier servidor estatico
```

`config.js` expone:
- `window.WISEPOCKET_API_BASE_URL`
- `window.KLARITY_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`

